args: What are you shouting about, Xander?

I am Saint Starfall, yes? But despite
graciously offering to deliver presents to
the peasants on this most auspicious
occasion, there is a dearth of said gifts!
How am I supposed to spread the\nblessings of Dragonyule now, I ask you?!
Actually, I think there's more to being\nSaint Starfall than delivering presents.
No, I'm serious. For example,\nyou could look for people in need\nand offer them a helping hand.
That's something Saint Starfall would do.
Hmm. I suppose it IS a king's duty to\nprovide charity to the various rabble.\nMy thanks, {player_name}!
I shall set forth and aid this castle's\ninhabitants with all speed!
Lay down your ladle and mop your\nclammy brow, laborer!
What did you just call me?\n...Also, what is all that food?
Why, this is my feast, of course! I know\nyou to be a rather busy individual, so I\ndid you the honor of cooking tonight.

Ha HA! Allay your suspicions, good
woman. If you are concerned about
how it tastes, you merely need to
try some yourself.
Well, if you insist... *munch*\nOh my goodness. This is incredible.
Of course! When your regent is involved,\nnothing less than the best will do.
Think of it as a gift from the gallant Saint\nStarfall himself. I pray you and all my\nother vassals take great succor from it.
This is certainly an unexpected kindness.\nBut if I may ask, where exactly did all\nof this food come from?
Where else but our larder?\nI used all that we had.

In truth, it made for a rather pitiful feast,
but ah well! Still, you must excuse me,
for there are others who even now cry
out for Saint Starfall's aid. Farewell!
Ugh. Now I have to go shopping AGAIN.
*sigh* This is getting me nowhere.\nThere must be a better way to train.
Consider your prayers answered, knave,\nfor Saint Starfall is here to help!
Permit your king to show you a better way\nto increase your strength!
Oh? I cannot help but feel apprehensive\nabout this—but very well.
Hmm? My feet suddenly feel heavier.\nWhat have you done, Xander?
I attached some weights to your greaves.\nThis is guaranteed to make your training\nmuch more productive.
Hnnngh! ...Yes, this does seem effective.\nYou have my thanks, Xander.
Think nothing of it. Everyone else rejected\nthem, so I am glad they were of use.
Alas, yes—but everything in this world has\na use, and a great king knows how to find\nit! Ha HA! Ha HA ha ha ha ha!
...Whew! That was exhausting—but it\nDOES feel as though it was productive.
Let me just remove these weights and...\nWhat?! Oh, blast! They require a KEY!
How dreadfully inconvenient—I see now\nwhy everyone else refused them.
Er, Xander? ...Xander?! Where are you?!\nI need the key to these weights!
...Wait. He LOCKED weights on your legs?
Indeed—and now everyone can hear my\nclomping approach from miles away.
*sigh* I'm sorry, Elly. I think this is all\nbecause of what I said to him.
You have no need to apologize,\nYour Highness.
Indeed, I rather admire the fact that he is\ntrying to bring happiness to others,\neven if he is somewhat...bad at it.
Xander just needs to be a little more\nconsiderate in how he goes about it.
Ah! A little birdie spoke my name!
Hello, Xander. We were just talking about\nhow you've been helping people lately.
Ha HA! A fine topic of discussion indeed.
In fact, I was just thinking that I should\nexpand the reach of my benevolence.
Why restrict myself to a castle when I can\ngrant my blessings to the outside world?
Now THAT is a task fit for a king!
Er, this sounds like it will be a lot of work\nfor one person. Maybe I should tag along.
How very considerate of you to offer!\nYou really are my number-one vassal.
I shall take you up on your proposal so you\nmight witness a true monarch in action.
Psst! Guys, if he seems like he's going to\ncause trouble, I'll do my best to stop him.
This marked the beginning of Xander and\n{player_name}'s long, eventful journe—
THE KEY! I forgot to ask him for it!\nXander, waaaaait!
